claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Partial first page of a clinical research article showing introductory text and a description of a repeat vaccination study comparing egg-based and cell-based influenza vaccines, with cohort size and exploratory immunogenicity analyses; no visible table or data on mutations. does not support the claim: the visible content provides study context and design but contains no information on production-related mutations or their effect on vaccine effectiveness. Note: Image is a partial page with the table cut off and some text slightly obscured, limiting full assessment.
